snippet.textDisplay:
The rolling races are always going to play into the hands of the Tesla because you're not testing rolling power but response then power. Normally people aren't sitting there off throttle then just mash it. Come out of a corner (or off an island etc) and you feed the throttle in which is when the turbos are already spinning.
Its pretty obvious that Audi is miles faster than that Tesla if you take the response out and even the fat Merc has much more once its going.

It’s cheaper as well, has stardew valley, twitch/Hulu and can drive itself to pick you up in the freezing rain.
